<subSubSection id="44FFB0EAFFBEFFA215DBFC98B71DFC10" pageId="21" pageNumber="246" type="description">
<paragraph id="0C5AE361FFBEFFA215DBFC98B34BFCAF" blockId="21.[151,1437,793,1288]" pageId="21" pageNumber="246">
<emphasis id="3E913F73FFBEFFA215DBFC98B7F2FCE7" box="[151,453,793,819]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="246">Female pregenital segment</emphasis>
. Posterior margin of sternite VII conically produced medially, with median very narrow lightly sclerotized area in distal half, in basal region grooved, median projection slightly shorter than length of sternite preceding it; median area dark brown widening posteriorly, lateral angles slightly posteriorly produced (
<figureCitation id="94DEFFE4FFBEFFA2105AFCE0B358FCAF" box="[1302,1391,865,891]" captionStart="FIGURES 4" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[158,1429,193,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-18@7.[158,1429,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 4 A–G. Species of Drabescus from Indian subcontinent. D. stramineus Distant, lectotype female: A, dorsal view; B, lateral view; C, face and thoracic sternites, ventral view; D, abdomen ventral view; E, data labels; F. Drabescus sp., nymph; G. D. limbaticephs (Stål), adult in natural habitat." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6479824" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6479824/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="246">Fig. 4D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0C5AE361FFBEFFA2158BFC07B71DFC10" blockId="21.[151,1437,793,1288]" pageId="21" pageNumber="246">
<emphasis id="3E913F73FFBEFFA2158BFC07B75EFC4B" box="[199,361,902,927]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="246">Measurements</emphasis>
. Female 
<quantity id="CB1D4E84FFBEFFA2149FFC04B41DFC74" box="[467,554,901,928]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.6" pageId="21" pageNumber="246" unit="mm" value="9.6">9.6 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity id="CB1D4E84FFBEFFA2173FFC04B4FDFC74" box="[627,714,901,928]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" pageId="21" pageNumber="246" unit="mm" value="3.5">3.5 mm</quantity>
wide across eyes and 
<quantity id="CB1D4E84FFBEFFA21685FC04B217FC74" box="[969,1056,901,928]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.2" pageId="21" pageNumber="246" unit="mm" value="3.2">3.2 mm</quantity>
wide across posterolateral angles of pronotum.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
